	    <tr>
	      <td >
		<p><a href="http://www.cisreg.ca/cgi-bin/oPOSSUM/opossum"><img src="index_files/human.gif" align="left" width="75" height="70"></a>
		  Human Single Site Analysis (SSA) is designed to detect over-represented conserved <b>single</b> sites in human and mouse genes.</p>
		<p class="caption">Reference: Ho Sui,	<i>et al.</i> (2005). oPOSSUM: Identification of over-represented 
		  transcription factor binding sites in co-expressed genes. <i>NAR</i>, 
		  33(10):3154-64. PMID: <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?db=pubmed&cmd=Retrieve&dopt=AbstractPlus&list_uids=15933209" target="new">15933209</a>
		</p>
	      </td>
	    </tr>
